        <h4 id="grey">Details</h4>
        
        <p><strong>Prep Time</strong> 20 minutes<br><strong>Cooking Time</strong>15 minutes <br><strong>Serves</strong>2 people <br>
        <strong>Cooking Temperature</strong>375¬∞F (190¬∞C) <br><strong>Equipment Needed:</strong>Mixing bowl, rolling pin, baking tray, oven <br>
</p>
<h5 id="or">Instructions</h5>
<ol>
    <li>Preheat your oven to 375¬∞F (190¬∞C)</li>
     <li>Mix the flour and water in a large mixing bowl to create the dough. Knead until smooth.</li>
      <li>Roll out the dough on a floured surface into a round shape.</li>
       <li>Spread the tomato sauce evenly over the dough.</li>
        <li>Add mozzarella cheese on top of the sauce.</li>
         <li>Drizzle a little olive oil over the pizza.</li>
          <li>Bake the pizza in the oven for about 15 minutes, or until the crust is golden and the cheese is melted.</li>
           <li>Once baked, add fresh basil leaves on top for extra flavor.</li>
    
</ol>
        
    
